tasks.title: [TASK] Phase 5: Migrate and Integrate Interface Layer

Update pyproject.toml with any new dependencies.

tasks.title: [BUG] `manage_subtask` MCP tool is not recognizing valid actions
tasks.description: The `manage_subtask` MCP tool is failing with an "Unknown subtask action" error for valid actions like `update_subtask` and `remove_subtask`. This prevents programmatic modification of subtasks, blocking orchestration workflows. The tool's server-side implementation needs to be investigated and fixed to correctly handle all documented actions.

subtasks.title: Verify the `manage_subtask` tool now correctly handles `update_subtask` and `remove_subtask` actions.

tasks.title: Integrate Task Management with FastMCP Server
tasks.description: Integrate the migrated task management module with the main FastMCP server architecture to expose task management capabilities through the unified server interface.
tasks.details:
**Objective**: Integrate the task management module with the main FastMCP server to provide unified access to task management capabilities.

**Integration Points**:
1. Main FastMCP server in `dhafnck_mcp_main/src/fastmcp/server/`
2. Task management MCP tools and routers
3. Server configuration and initialization
4. Error handling and middleware integration

**Tasks**:
- Analyze current FastMCP server architecture
- Identify integration points for task management
- Update server initialization to include task management routes
- Ensure proper error handling and middleware integration
- Test server startup and functionality

**Dependencies**: 
- Requires "Complete Interface Layer Migration" task to be completed first

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- Task management MCP tools accessible through main FastMCP server
- Server starts successfully with task management integrated
- All existing FastMCP functionality remains intact
- Task management endpoints respond correctly
- Proper error handling and logging in place

tasks.title: Create Migration Integration Tests
tasks.description: Develop comprehensive integration tests to validate that the migrated task management module works correctly within the FastMCP framework and maintains all expected functionality.
tasks.details:
**Objective**: Create comprehensive integration tests to ensure the migrated task management module functions correctly within the FastMCP ecosystem.

**Test Scope**:
1. **MCP Tools Testing**: Verify all MCP tools work correctly
2. **API Endpoint Testing**: Test all task management endpoints
3. **Domain Logic Testing**: Validate core business logic still works
4. **Integration Testing**: Ensure proper integration with FastMCP server
5. **Regression Testing**: Confirm no functionality lost in migration

**Test Categories**:
- Unit tests for migrated components
- Integration tests for MCP server interaction
- End-to-end tests for complete workflows
- Performance tests to ensure no degradation
- Error handling and edge case tests

**Dependencies**:
- Requires "Complete Interface Layer Migration" to be completed
- Requires "Integrate Task Management with FastMCP Server" to be completed

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- All critical functionality tested and working
- Test coverage >= 80% for migrated code
- All tests pass consistently
- Performance benchmarks meet or exceed original
- Comprehensive test documentation created
- CI/CD integration tests configured

tasks.title: Migration Validation and Documentation
tasks.description: Perform final validation of the migration, update documentation, and ensure the migrated task management module is production-ready within the FastMCP framework.
tasks.details:
**Objective**: Complete final validation and documentation to ensure the migration is production-ready and properly documented.

**Validation Tasks**:
1. **Code Quality Review**: Review all migrated code for quality and consistency
2. **Architecture Validation**: Ensure DDD principles maintained
3. **Performance Validation**: Verify performance meets requirements
4. **Security Review**: Check for security implications of migration
5. **Documentation Update**: Update all relevant documentation

**Documentation Updates**:
- Update FastMCP documentation to include task management
- Create migration guide for future reference
- Update API documentation with new endpoints
- Create troubleshooting guide
- Update README files and examples

**Final Checks**:
- All dependencies properly listed in pyproject.toml
- No dead code or unused imports
- Proper error handling throughout
- Logging and monitoring configured
- Security best practices followed

**Dependencies**:
- Requires all previous migration tasks to be completed
- Requires integration tests to pass

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- Code quality review completed and approved
- All documentation updated and accurate
- Performance benchmarks documented
- Security review completed
- Migration officially complete and production-ready

tasks.title: [EPIC] Migration Production Readiness - Phase 6 & 7 Completion
tasks.description: Epic to complete the final phases of the migration from cursor_agent to dhafnck_mcp_main, focusing on production readiness through comprehensive testing (Phase 6 completion) and dependency management (Phase 7). Based on the migration plan analysis showing 70% completion, this epic addresses the remaining 30% needed for production deployment.

subtasks.title: Fix project orchestration datetime parsing issue
subtasks.description: Fixed datetime parsing error in _convert_to_project_entity method that was causing 'str' object cannot be interpreted as an integer error

tasks.title: [TASK] Phase 7: Dependency Management & Integration
tasks.description: Merge critical dependencies from cursor_agent/pyproject.toml to dhafnck_mcp_main/pyproject.toml. Key missing dependencies identified: jsonschema>=4.17.0 (for task validation), psutil>=5.9.0 (for system monitoring). PyYAML is already available. Resolve version conflicts, optimize dependency tree, and ensure security compliance. This is critical for production readiness as missing dependencies may cause runtime failures in advanced task management features.

subtasks.title: Install and test jsonschema>=4.17.0
subtasks.description: Add jsonschema dependency to dhafnck_mcp_main/pyproject.toml and test task validation functionality

subtasks.title: Install and test psutil>=5.9.0
subtasks.description: Add psutil dependency to dhafnck_mcp_main/pyproject.toml and test system monitoring capabilities

subtasks.title: Resolve dependency version conflicts
subtasks.description: Audit all dependencies for conflicts and optimize dependency tree for production stability

tasks.title: [TASK] Phase 6: Performance Benchmarking & Validation
tasks.description: Create comprehensive performance benchmarking suite comparing migrated implementation against original cursor_agent performance. Test all MCP tool response times, task operations (create, update, delete), multi-agent orchestration scenarios, and memory usage profiling. Establish performance baselines and ensure no regression >5%. Critical for production readiness validation.

tasks.title: [TASK] Phase 6: Cross-Platform Compatibility Testing
tasks.description: Validate dhafnck_mcp_main task management functionality across different platforms and Python versions. Test on Windows, macOS, Linux with Python 3.10, 3.11, 3.12. Verify virtual environment isolation, dependency resolution, and MCP server startup/shutdown procedures. Ensure consistent behavior across all supported platforms for production deployment.

tasks.title: [TASK] Phase 6: Stress Testing & Scalability Validation
tasks.description: Conduct stress testing for large-scale scenarios: 1000+ tasks, multi-agent orchestration under load, concurrent access patterns, and error recovery validation. Test task hierarchy management, subtask operations, and agent assignment at scale. Validate memory usage, response times, and system stability under production-like loads. Critical for production deployment confidence.

tasks.title: [TASK] Phase 7: Security Audit & Compliance Review
tasks.description: Conduct comprehensive security audit of migrated task management system. Review all dependencies for security vulnerabilities, validate input sanitization in MCP tools, test authentication and authorization mechanisms, and ensure compliance with security standards. Run security scanners (bandit, safety) and address any critical or high-severity issues. Essential for production deployment approval.

tasks.title: [TASK] Phase 7: Code Quality & Standards Alignment
tasks.description: Ensure migrated code aligns with fastmcp coding standards. Complete type hint coverage >80%, apply consistent code formatting (black, isort), run linting (flake8, mypy), and optimize performance bottlenecks. Update documentation to match fastmcp standards, ensure API consistency, and validate import path optimization. Final code quality gate before production deployment.

tasks.title: [TASK] Production Deployment Preparation & Validation
tasks.description: Final preparation for production deployment of migrated task management system. Create deployment guides, validate CI/CD pipeline integration, test production-like environment setup, and conduct final end-to-end validation. Ensure all success metrics are met: >80% test coverage, <5% performance regression, zero critical security issues, and complete documentation. Final go/no-go decision for production release.
